On 8/19/2020 I encountered I think one of the rudest Managers ever.  I had purchased a salad at Simple Green and wasn't aware the tables on the street were for the business customers only (it was 1:15 pm NO ONE was eating outside, but me).  The 1st time the manager informed me the tables were for the business patrons only, I shared "I'm sorry, I was not aware", I continued to finish my lunch.  He returned, this time very rude.  I said to him, that he wasn't clear the 1st time that he wanted me to leave.  So I gathered my unfinished salad and left.  He walked away with his back turned to me mumbled something I could not make out.   I even called to speak to the manager on duty . . . the employee I encountered picked up the phone and his attitude got worse.  I ask if I could speak to someone else, his exact word were, "this is as high as you'll get" OMG!!!  I'm a HR Manger and would never allow my team to speak to a customer like this.  Unacceptable behavior during times like these.  I'll reach out to Department of Consumer and Regulatory Affairs to report as well.  OMG!!!!

It’s been four years since I’ve been here, but I still think about this burger fairly often, as it’s easily one of the top 10 burgers I’ve had in my life. The grilled cheese was wonderful, and the house ale was good - though I don’t really remember the rate so much as I remember liking it. As I recall, it was a bit crowded when I was there, but this can hardly be held against them (it was about forty minutes after most workplaces had gotten out), and should, in fact, be looked at as a testament to how amazing this place is. And the prices aren’t that bad, either! Stoney’s has easily become one of my DC favorites, and I can’t wait until the day when I get to visit the city again… I know where I’m going for dinner that first night!

On Sunday me and my nephew driving around hungry looking for a place to eat. I stopped Stoney's loved the name. He turns around and find parking at whole foods. Checked out the menu attached to the window. Love the prices and the type of food being served. My nephew was a skeptic, he likes being served and when you entered it was seat yourself but within three minutes of finding a seat our waitress was front and center and excellent. Her recommendation was good appetizer nachos built for two and the Alfredo off the roof. The drink White Russian made to specification kudos to the bartender, cook and my waitress. All is well at Stoney's. Definitely a bon appetit!
